 TUNIT3  = 'percent '           / physical unit of field                         
 TTYPE4  = 'error   '           / label for field   4                            
 TFORM4  = '1200E   '           / data format of field: 4-byte REAL              
 TUNIT4  = 'percent '           / physical unit of field                         
 EXTNAME = 'polarimetry'        / name of this binary table extension            
 CALIBRAT= 'pbo3aB  '           / Instrumental polarization calibration used     
 AVE-POL =                0.053 / Mean %Pol over entire wavelength region        
 AVE-ERRO=                0.002 / Mean %Error in %Pol                            
 AVE-PA  =                45.35 / [deg] Mean Position Angle                      
 UX-POL  =                0.117 / Synthetic UX Filter %Polarization              
 UX-ERR  =                0.011 / Synthetic UX Filter %Error                     
 UX-PA   =                57.22 / [deg] Synthetic UX Filter Position Angle       
 B-POL   =                0.060 / Synthetic B Filter %Polarization               
 B-ERR   =                0.003 / Synthetic B Filter %Error                      
 B-PA    =                51.06 / [deg] Synthetic B Filter Position Angle        
 V-POL   =                0.048 / Synthetic V Filter %Polarization               
 V-ERR   =                0.002 / Synthetic V Filter %Error                      
 V-PA    =                41.63 / [deg] Synthetic V Filter Position Angle        
 R-POL   =                0.063 / Synthetic R Filter %Polarization               
 R-ERR   =                0.001 / Synthetic R Filter %Error                      
 R-PA    =                39.02 / [deg] Synthetic R Filter Position Angle        
 I-POL   =                0.062 / Synthetic I Filter %Polarization               
 I-ERR   =                0.002 / Synthetic I Filter %Error                      
 I-PA    =                38.76 / [deg] Synthetic I Filter Position Angle        
 COMMENT The errors given in the error array are the statistical errors          
 COMMENT based on the residuals of the least squared fit to the four             
 COMMENT filter-pair polarimetric data (see section 2.3 of Wolff,                
 COMMENT Nordsieck & Nook 1996 AJ 111, 856).                                     
 COMMENT The polarimetric stability is 0.002% and less than +/- 0.03             
 COMMENT degrees in position angle. See Harries et al. 2000, A&A, 361, 273       
 COMMENT for more information about the HPOL CCD.                                
 COMMENT HPOL CCD instrumental polarization has been removed.                    
 COMMENT ***IMPORTANT NOTE***                                                    
 COMMENT **The ERROR array is also being used as a QUALITY array.                
 COMMENT **For bad/contaminated data, the errors have been set to zero           
 COMMENT **but the %Q & %U arrays for those wavelengths remain unchanged         
 COMMENT **to allow inspection of the bad data.                                  
 COMMENT **All of the arrays except wavelength have been padded with zeroes at   
 COMMENT **the short and long wavelength ends indicating no useful data.         
